| Trivia                  = * The real American Mafia no longer dominates organized crime in the United States. Outside of the northeast (mainly NY City) and in Chicago (mostly the suburbs) where the Mafia is still strong, the criminal underworld is dominated by other groups and in many major cities the American Mafia no longer have a presence.{{r|{{cite web|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Mafia|title=American Mafia|date=9 June 2020|accessdate=9 June 2020}}}}{{r|{{cite web|url=https://apnews.com/d205853aca1e47c2816f8bb5b0300f30/The-last-Mafioso?-%27Cadillac-Frank%27-trial-shows-mob%27s-decline|title=The last Mafioso? ‘Cadillac Frank’ trial shows mob’s decline|work=Associated Press|first=Alanna|last=Durkin Richer|date=17 June 2018|accessdate=9 June 2020}}}}{{r|{{cite web|url=https://www.journals.uchicago.edu/doi/pdfplus/10.1086/706895|title=The Rise and Fall of Organized Crime in the United States|work=University of Chicago Press|first=James|last=B. Jacobs|date=18 November 2019|accessdate=9 June 2020}}}}{{r|{{cite web|url=https://qz.com/1574849/weve-got-a-gig-mafia-now-what-a-mob-bosss-murder-tells-us|title=“We’ve got a gig Mafia now”: What a mob boss’s murder tells us|work=Quartz|first=Lila|last=MacLellan|date=16 March 2019|accessdate=9 June 2020}}}}
